result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordan D Fairbairn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jordan D Fairbairn in court with attorney J. Dennis Thornton.  Defendant Jordan D Fairbairn in custody.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

Court sentenced defendant to serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 30 days served FOR A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION. 

Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by 03-21-2016 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
Defendant is Remanded into Custody of the Sheriff Department.

Defendant Jordan D Fairbairn in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Defendant Jordan D Fairbairn in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: LM  
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Judge, Branch 21.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 19, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Notice of bond forfeiture mailed to defendant; Original in file. ($150.00 signature bond) ad
Signature bond ordered to be forfeited in the amount of 150.00.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE BENCH  WARRANT.

Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask in court earlier.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant to be issued.  State's motion for Judgment of Bond Forfeiture 30 days after notification from Clerk of Circuit Court's Office is granted by the Court.

Defendant Jordan D Fairbairn in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

PENALTY ENHANCER:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered the penalty enhancer, 'USE OF A DANGEROUS WEAPON', stricken from the record.

AS TO THE AMENDED CHARGE:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 24.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 5, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant's Requested Jury Instructions received and filed.
Motion in Limine received and filed.
Defense Witness List received and filed.
Defendant's Demand for Discovery and Inspection received and filed.

Defendant Jordan D Fairbairn in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Court reiterated the no contact order.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 28, 2015 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for May 20, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jordan D Fairbairn in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Matter scheduled for plea/sentencing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for March 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with CHELSEA F. AND CHRISTOPHER R.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
